         <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.5685" xml:lang="en">
            <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
            <dateline>Göttingen<lb/>Weender Strasse 57<lb/>May 5. 1871</dateline>
            <p>I am going to surprise you. I have to leave here in a few days. I have just accepted an inspectorship of schools in Wales. It is good pay but I do not yet know how much time is left to one for one’s own studies. I hope you have had my last note addressed to Gotha but as <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> I am doubtful about it I will not send the Bible till I hear from you I shall not be leaving till Tuesday or Wednesday I think I hope this change in my whereabouts will make no difference whatever in our correspondence. Would you favour me with a word in a day or two.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>I remain</salute>
               <lb/>
               <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
               <lb/>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">J. Rhŷs</persName>
               </signed>
            </closer>
         </div>
